OL,3,CBrother fears another child will die
OL,4,Cif The Scouts continue to self-regulate
OL,6,FThe inquest heard that the scout
OL,7,Fleaders on that trip had not had
OL,8,Fadequate safety training.
OL,10,FThere had been no risk assessment
OL,11,Fbefore the trip up The Great Orme and
OL,12,Fnone of the leaders was a qualified
OL,13,Ffirst-aider - which meant the trip
OL,14,Fshould not have gone ahead in the
OL,15,Ffirst place.
OL,17,FThe families of children who died
OL,18,Fwhile on organised Scout trips have
OL,19,Fstarted a petition calling for a
OL,20,FPublic Inquiry into the Scout
OL,21,FAssociation.
