OL,3,CBrother fears another child will die
OL,4,Cif The Scouts continue to self-regulate
OL,6,FBen's brother Tom believes if there is
OL,7,Fnot a public inquiry, and with The
OL,8,FScouts are allowed to continue to
OL,9,Fregulate themselves, other children
OL,10,Fmay die.
OL,12,FTom said: "Their entire behaviour
OL,13,Fthroughout this five-and-a-half years
OL,14,Fwas: 'Do you not know who are? How
OL,15,Fdare you? We're The Scouts'.
OL,17,F"The reality of it all finally hit me
OL,18,Ftwo or three weeks ago. The fact that
OL,19,Fhe is dead and the reality of what The
OL,20,FScouts have done. It's a very absurd
OL,21,Fand horrific situation.
