OL,3,CBrother fears another child will die
OL,4,Cif The Scouts continue to self-regulate
OL,6,FSharon said: "Currently the Scouts
OL,7,Fself regulate, so whatever happens, if
OL,8,Fthere's a serious incident a critical
OL,9,Fincident, they will be responsible to
OL,10,Fexplore and and investigate that
OL,11,Fincident.
OL,13,F"When things go wrong (on a Scout
OL,14,Ftrip) they can hide it, brush it under
OL,15,Fthe carpet ... when what should happen
OL,16,Fis that they have a duty of candour"
OL,18,FThe first two inquests into Ben's
OL,19,Fdeath were halted after The Scout
OL,20,FAssociation withheld evidence.
